    • Constructor Detail

      • Links

        public Links()
        Creates a new Links instance connection to the localhost and default port of MongoDB. This constructor enables to start the application with the selection of the experiment name.

      • Links

        public Links(java.lang.String xpName)
        Creates a new Links instance connection to the localhost and default port of MongoDB. This constructor intializes the experiment to the name passed in parameter.
        Parameters:
        xpName - The name of the experiment to use. If an experiment with this name already exists, the application restore the previously loaded data.

      • Links

        public Links(com.mongodb.ServerAddress addr,
             java.lang.String xpName)
        Creates a new Links instance connection to the specified address of MongoDB. This constructor intialise the experiment to the name passed in parameter.
        Parameters:
        addr - The ServerAddress of the MongoDB database.
        xpName - The name of the experiment to use. If an experiment with this name already exists, the application restore the previously loaded data.
